animal.description:
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Omega and I'm a one-eyed wonder. I have been through a lot and while it is visible with scars on my body, I'm hoping to find a new family that can look past the physical and see what a good girl I am and accept all the love I have to give. My foster mom showed me what it is like to be inside a home, to receive love and attention - I didn't know it could feel so good! I will reciprocate with kisses, cuddles and loyalty. 
I would do best with a person or family who is home a lot because I don't like to be left alone and have some separation anxiety - but I'm getting better! I get along well with other dogs and having a buddy helps keep me company and calm when my foster mom needs to leave the house. A home where I can be with the family and not kept separate would make me so happy. If/when needed, I do well in a gated area where I can still see out, but I don't like to be crated. I am a lower energy dog but love my daily walks and the opportunity to run and stretch my legs. I walk well on a leash and will try to run after squirrels, but I am easily redirected. I like to play with toys, throwing them in the air and also love to crawl up to you and cuddle up on the couch. 
For bedtime, I stay in my spot and sleep through the night. I have been so good that my foster mom now lets me sleep in her room (in my bed) or even lets me stay on the couch in the next room when I choose to sleep there. I started to learn how to alert my foster mom when I need to go outside; I will sit next to the door or come to her and press my nose - I haven't had a potty accident for several weeks now!
 A few other things to know about me; I am scared of sudden movements and loud noises. I am shy/nervous around new people and it can take me a bit to get used to them, but I will just stay by you until I feel comfortable. I haven't chewed on anything except my toys, but when I am left alone, I will be curious and look through your mail or if it's accessible, I will take things out of the garbage or open cabinets if there are treats inside. I also might take food off the counter/table if I can reach it (and get away with it) - but I'm really good at listening and understand a gentle "No". I come when called and I'm learning how to sit for my food and treats! If you have cats, I am good with them too - they are interesting to watch.
Omega is currently living with a volunteer foster family. Fill out this form https://forms.gle/pj317JttC7s38ibQA if you are interested in meeting her!

animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Negrita is a beautiful 1-year-old Chihuahua blend who weighs approximately 17 pounds. Negrita was found as a stray in a small town in Mexico where she faced a sad life of starvation and abuse. A Good Samaritan in that area stepped in to change her fate and contacted our rescue for assistance. Negrita initially is shy but once your offer her treats, she quickly displays her affectionate and loyal nature. Negrita prefers the company of humans over other dogs and would do well as an only dog. Additionally, she will require leash training.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
Her adoption fee is $200. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, Tri-Heart Plus chewable tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description: My name is The Hotness and it's nice to make your acquaintance. While my name is bigger than life, I'm still shy when meeting new people. Being caught running on the street was very hard for me, and it took a little time to realize that these people were here to help. But I've made a lot of friends here now, and I'm ready to start my new life! I am searching for a patient owner with a relaxed lifestyle who can help build my confidence. We may need to take things really slow at first while I get to know you. You wouldn't want to be picked up by a stranger either, right? Because I can get scared, kids and (most) other dogs aren't really my thing. But with the help of my circle of friends at the shelter, I'm learning how to be OK hanging out near other dogs, and meeting new people! When I'm comfortable you'll see just how much I live up to my stylish name; I'm guaranteed to keep you smiling with my clownish antics. Want to talk to my friends and see if I might be the dog for you? animal.description: Scarlet is a 2 year old, 60lb, spayed female. Scarlet is a shelter favorite but it has been challenging to find the right forever home for her. Scarlet's needs are pretty specifica home with plenty of room to run but no small children, cats or chickens and she is selective about other dogs. Scarlet is also an escape artist and finding a fence that could contain her has been an issue. Scarlet's extended stay has taken its toll on her and she was starting to become increasingly unwelcoming to visitors while in her kennel. We have reached the end of our ability to provide for Scarlet's mental and emotional needs. The Friends of Cookeville Putnam County Animals and the SAVEUS club at Tennessee Tech coordinated Scarlet's entering Thunderhawk's 4 week training program. Scarlet will remain available for adoption while at Thunderhawk. We hope that the right adopter will come along while Scarlet is at Thunderhawk so the trainers can work with Scarlet and her adopter for a smooth transition into Scarlet's forever home. Watch Scarlet's progress at https://www.facebook.com/ThunderHawkK9/ and contact the shelter if you would like to make an appointment to meet her.

animal.description:
This amazing jokester is the full package—athletic, smart, spry, fun-loving, obedient and young enough to take on the world right by your side!  

Please meet Ruff Patch!  He is an American Bulldog mix weighing in at 60 lbs of total cuteness!  He was found as a stray in Memphis, Tennessee. He had been attacked by other dogs and was very emaciated. His physical wounds have all healed, but he still is a bit wary of other dogs from time to time. He loves attention, cuddling on the couch and chasing a ball!  He loves playing outside and is learning a few manners along the way. He still likes to help you cook, if you will let him, and he can find every morsel that you drop. He is learning commands, is learning leash manners and loves to ride in a car. He will try to get out with you, just in case you need help, and riding shotgun is super fun!  He is housebroken and crate trained, but consistency is key to his continued training. He loves to play with friends and take leisurely strolls patrolling the yard. He ABSOLUTELY ADORES TOYS, especially those that squeak and crinkle. You will most likely find him in a toy box, if given the chance.  He has an adorable personality, especially once he gets to know you and settles in. He would love going on hikes, spending the day at the beach or sitting by a bonfire. Whatever the adventure, he is your man!  Due to his history of being attacked, and while he is currently living with other foster dogs, we believe he would be happiest and most settled in a home without other dogs. One where his new family can devote all their attention and love to him. 

If you are interested in this adorable, loving, adventurous young man, please get your apps in as fast as you can!

THE APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PICTURE. 


ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Ruff Patch
Breed:  American Bulldog mix
Gender:  Male         
Age:  1 year       
Weight: 60 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes       
Vaccines: Current                      
Heartworm:  Tested positive on 1/5/2021, currently on Heartgard, and will be treated on 2/8-9/2021
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with dogs of various sizes, breeds and genders, but we think he would prefer being an only dog. 
Cats:  Unknown
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, He has NOT been tested with infants or toddlers, so proper supervision and introductions would be required. 

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our animals are fostered in various locations in the a South and in New England. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers who work full-time jobs and have animals of our own, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description:
Jack came to us as part of our Traveling Tails Program. He is looking for a home that will offer a steady routine. He's very active and would strive in a home that is as eager to spend time outdoors as he is. His GO, GO, GO mentality will need to be met with a serious commitment to providing him with adequate physical and mental stimulation.

Unfortunately Jack has never met another dog. Both the fear of the unknown and excitement around other dogs causes Jack to be quite reactive around them. At this time, we do not think he would do well with another dog in the home. With slow, positive introductions, Jack may someday learn that other dogs can be quite fun. An adult only home with no other animals would be ideal for him.

Jack is still learning to cope with being by himself in a home setting. Jack will whine and bark when left alone before he settles. A detached home or very understanding neighbors will be necessary for a successful placement.

animal.description:
Putt Putt is a hole in one!

This little guy was picked up as a stray, but he is ready for a new home of his own. This delicate little guy is ready to warm your lap while you work from home and get you out for short little walks. He'd also fit perfectly in a dog pack on hikes. 

Here are some great notes from his foster:
Putt Putt, (AKA Putters) is a little darling. He's a somber fella, with no aggression in him whatsoever. He loves nothing more than being wrapped in a blanket, lounging and living the life of relaxation. 

When he first arrived with us he had numerous health issues and was very nervous, but after surgery, medication and getting used to us he's found a new lease of life, albeit a tame one.

He loves to go on walks in his cute tartan jacket, half a block does the trick to satisfy his curiosity and fondness for building entrance ways, other dogs and trying to scale objects outside his range. 

Despite his love for adventure, Putters is very wobbly on his legs, his own shakes often topple him which means you have to be extra careful. It doesn't stop him though and you'll often hear him tippy tapping around the house getting his laps in.

Putt Putt would do very well in a relaxed home with somebody older who wants a cute pal to enjoy. He would LOVE a companion dog, but due to his legs he's best suited with a dog that wouldn't knock him over or try and wrestle. Perhaps an equally senior doggo?

For the right patient person, Putt Putt is a delight and would bring a heap of joy to the family!

animal.description:
Wee long haired chi Ivy is in search of a forever lap. She has PhD level lap sitting skills; all she needs is a full time opportunity to show them off. Do you have a position available? She's also silky soft, perfect for petting, and sweet as can be. Plus she's lived with cats and dogs! Ivy is sure to be hired quickly; put in your application today!

* HERE'S WHAT IVY'S FOSTER MOM HAS TO SAY! *

Sweet, soft girl Ivy has taken some time to adjust to our home on busy Van Ness Ave in SF! She has a sweet, affectionate disposition spending her days snoozing and looking for warm beds to snuggle in. She is slowly becoming more brave and will venture out to explore the apartment but definitely appreciates having a bed in a safe little "corner" to dart back to, like a furry little Roomba returning to it's charging station!

Ivy is still a little intimidated by new people and new streets, so she may prefer a home in a quieter location. She has learned to walk a few blocks at a time, but is happy to be scooped into your arms or a purse to stay out of the way of scary feet, bicycles and scooters. 
She hasn't barked yet but makes small noises to show when she wants to be let out for potty which she does on the grass, with some encouragement. Don't be concerned if she runs away from the leash at first- leash walking is new for her and she's still adjusting to it! 

In the right home, Ivy will need a little patience and practice in "how to dog". She responds very well with encouragement, but needs a little practice following on leash ("please carry me mom!") and eating at scheduled meal times. She loves her dog beds but probably wants to be buried under your sheets and on your sofa more :)

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

A REAL STORY TO TELL. Mr. Bean is a three-year-old shepherd mix who, in a lot of ways, is still a puppy even though he weighs 42 pounds. Until very recently, this friendly, sweet-natured boy didn't get the training or care he needed and deserved. He lived outside and was never house- or leash trained. His original owners had to relocate unexpectedly and were unable to take him with them. Mr. Bean really hit the jackpot with his temporary home. He's learning about house training and walking on a leash, and he just loves his bed, treats and toys. Most of all, he loves sniffing around the backyard, getting petted and holding hands with his people. This family also took Mr. Bean to the vet for a long overdue checkup. Now he's up to date on vaccinations and is on flea/tick prevention. Unfortunately, Mr. Bean is heartworm positive, and he has an injury to one of his rear legs that possibly will require surgery. He also needs to be neutered. His temporary guardians have two dogs of their own and cannot take on a third. They've already done so much, and they are willing to contribute more for Mr. Bean's care, but what this sweet guy needs more than anything is a forever home with an individual, couple or family who will take responsibility for loving, training and caring for him. Although somewhat cautious at first with one of his foster brothers, Mr. Bean is comfortable with his fellow canines. Despite his lack of house training, he's learning and hasn't had any accidents. If you are willing to help Mr. Bean on the road to recovery, please fill out an application online at
tireddogrescue.org
. You won't be alone. TDR will do everything we can to assist you, including rallying support for Mr. Bean's medical care. Available through Tired Dog Rescue, Gulfport, MS.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Do you have a confident friendly dog in your family? Would you like to add a pretty, smart and active pup? Then Blanca could be for you! Blanca is a 'high energy' type of girl who thinks her main goal in life is to explore (and taste) everything! She will do best with a family who is ready to steer her curiosity and enthusiam toward fun training and playing activities. She is not a fan of being separated from her humans and we feel another dog in her home for companionship will help a lot so we are making that a requirement. Blanca's Mom is just 20 pounds so she probably won't grow too much bigger than that. She is working on house training and just loves getting out and running around in the fenced yard with her foster siblings. If you think you have the right home for Blanca, don't hesitate to apply at www.sadiesrescue.org

Please keep in mind there are many factors to consider when choosing the right match for a puppy, so an application cannot guarantee adoption. Nor do we work on a 'first come first served' basis, but rather strive to find the best match for the personality of each dog. At the time of adoption, the puppy will be current on vaccinations and deworming. He or she will come with a pre-scheduled appointment at our vet to be spayed or neutered that the adopter is obligated to keep. The puppy will also be microchipped at this time Our puppy adoption fee is $350 plus a $50 training deposit, which is refunded to the adopter when he or she provides proof of having completed a basic obedience class with their puppy. As part of our adoption process, references both personal and veterinarian will be checked. Sadie's also requires a home visit before we adopt any of our dogs out; therefore we only adopt to our local WNY region.

animal.description:
BooBoo is one of the sweetest dogs you will ever have. It is a pleasure to be in his company and just being around him will put you in a better mood. When he first arrived at the shelter we already knew he was a special boy, he has those eyes that let you know what a kind soul he has. He has a calm, mild-mannered personality that would love to lay around and just be by your side during a relaxing day. He does enjoy running around the yard and plays well with other dogs. BooBoo loves going out in the mornings to play with his friend, but after a bit of playing they are both already calmed down just enjoying being with each other. If you need one of those special dogs that you won't ever forget come see BooBoo and bring your dogs and kids to make sure everyone gets along before adopting. We look forward to seeing you!

BooBoo is a 5-year-old male Pit Bull that weighs 74 pounds. He will be neutered and microchipped before going home and will stay at the shelter until he is neutered. He is current on his vaccinations, flea, and parasite prevention.

animal.description:
Bentley is a male pit bull terrier mix approximately one year old with a sweet disposition who likes nothing better than to cuddle with his humans. He first met his foster family when he came over to check out their two female dogs while
they were being walked on a Saturday morning in late December of 2020. He is playful, yet virtually never barks (we’ve heard him produce a single bark only one time). Though very curious, he also is readily trainable: he has completed house training (going out every three to four hours to take care of business), and his crate training is going well. He walks well on a leash, and has shown no aggression of any kind, including food-based (though he certainly is food-attentive—!). Despite loving his foster family, he still would like very much to find a loving human to call his own.

All dogs come with a microchip, annual vaccinations including EBR rabies license and tag, dewormer, vet exam and spay/neuter. Adoption fee is $95 - $175.

Baton Rouge, LA  70820  

phone: 225-408-5360

animal.description:
For auld lang syne, my dear
For auld lang syne
We’ll tak a cup o’ kindness yet
For days of auld lang syne. 

Meet the New Year’s Litter!  Auld, Lang and Syne were surrendered to our rescue after being found in a field. They were emaciated, scared and had skin issues, but they are doing great now. They are looking for their forever homes to start the New Year off right!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are crate trained and are working on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency, patience and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER HOMEPAGE. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Syne
Breed:  Lab mix
Gender:  Female
Age:  7 months
Weight: 15 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Tested Negative 1/15/21, currently on Heartgard 
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.

animal.description:
Leon Bear is a middled aged chow chow who entered a shelter as a stray and was not claimed by his owner. Like most chow chows, he was not very happy in the shelter that was loud and strange and filled with people he did not know. He did start warming up to staff in a few days. After transferring to us and getting to his foster home, Leon Bear quickly bonded with his foster parents. He likes to follow them around, be petted and roll around on their laps! He is very food motivated and loves to sit for cookies! He cannot have stuffed animals because he will gaurd them. 

For Leon Bear, we are looking for an adopter who has experience with chow chows. He will need a few days to bond with and be comfortable around a new family. Leon is so happy and affectionate and good natured once he gets to know you!

Augusta Dog Adoptions is an all- volunteer, foster- based rescue. We take applications online and are scheduling individual adoptions in the Waynesboro, VA area during the pandemic.  A $175.00 adoption fee ($300 for puppies under 6 months old) helps us take care of all the dogs we rescue. All dogs are spayed/neutered, tested for heartworm and tick borne diseases (if old enough), microchipped, and vaccinated for rabies (if old enough), distemper/parvo and bordetella. They are also treated for internal and external parasites. Many dogs also receive extensive medical care such as dental work and major surgeries. For more information and to apply to adopt, please visit www.augustadogadoptions.org

animal.description:
Age: 1yr
Weight: 75lbs and losing
Gender: Male
Energy Level: Moderate to High
Overall Drive: Moderate
Location: Eugene, OR
NO CATS, SMALL ANIMALS

Tungsten is a young, active dog who is eager to please and ready to learn. If he were a human, he’d be an athlete; always ready to play, no matter what the game!

Tungsten is very social and has done well meeting new people both inside and outside of the home without hesitation. He can be a bit over the top, so he needs reminders not to jump. Tungsten has been friendly with young children but due to his size would likely do best living with older children. Due to his prey drive, he will need a home without cats, livestock, or other small pets. Tungsten has done well with both male and female dogs (though prefers to play with females) after proper introductions, though his play style is very rough which can be off-putting for some. He rides well in a crate in the car, is curious about loud noises but not afraid, and is fully crate trained. Tungsten is working on basic obedience and will need a confident handler who is comfortable giving him firm correction and strong enough to keep him controlled if something catches his eye that he’d like to give chase to. He is currently working on reducing reactivity to cars while on-leash. Tungsten in many ways is your typical, young Malinois, a little mouthy in a playful way but always looking to his handler for guidance and support.

Tungsten needs a home ready for a full-sized dog with the energy and manners of your typical bouncy puppy. He will need an experienced handler who is ready to provide structure and boundaries along with plenty of affection and play. Tungsten’s nature would lend him well to being a running, hiking, or even swimming partner in the future. This giant puppy is ready to jump right into your heart – just in time for Valentine’s day!


WEST COAST ADOPTIONS ONLY

Must have previous or current, purebred Malinois experience OR other high drive working breed experience

Our adoption process includes- completion of an application, followed by a telephone interview. If that goes well, we will arrange for a home visit.
Adoption Fee: $500.00. Transport along Interstate 5 (Bakersfield, CA to Bellingham, WA) is available but cost not included in adoption fee. 

Please visit www.woofproject.org and fill out an adoption application located here https://www.woofproject.org/application

animal.description: Arya is 4 years old, loves people and kids! She likes to cuddle on the couch with you and sleep in her bed beside yours at night. She is not a barker! She finds that completely unnecessary unless you knock at the door and then she is excited to greet you! Housebroken - she will let you know when she really needs to go out. Low shedding. She loves when you brush her. She enjoys her walks but still shy of the outdoor environment... mmhh at least some places... She loves to go to the park and the Beach!! She is scared of other dogs, so needs to be the only pet in your house. She LOVES car rides! Very disciplined in the house and doesn't steal food or try to do any damage to your furniture. When you are at work she sleeps waiting for you to come home. SHE IS TRULY A LIFE COMPANION! Please complete your application to foster or adopt prior to our events. You will receive an email following your submission. If you don't receive that email you may need to use a different web server or work directly from a computer rather than a phone. Applications are processed during the week. Please give us time to contact your vet and references . Please submit an application at ruffhouserescue.org/foster or ruffhouserescue.com/adopt. Adoption events are held every weekend by appointment. Dogs in foster can be met during the week with their fosters by appointment. Our goal is to make the best match for every family. When attending an adoption event, we ask that the entire family/household attend as well as any family dogs.

animal.description:
Bailey – Boxer mix – 4yrs. – female (40 lbs.)

This adorable little gal has had a very hard life. She lived her entire life on a chain having puppies. Animal control found her at the end of that chain in a near death condition. She had a severe case of pyometra and a grapefruit-sized mammary mass. The poor thing could not walk or even lift her head. They took her off that chain and straight to their clinic... remarkably she survived and recovered very well! We took her from that shelter and are committed to making sure that the rest of her life is happy, carefree, and full of love – no more chains! Bailey is loving and sweet. She loves to go for walks and see the world. She plays with other dogs, but can be somewhat bossy so we believe that a good-sized male will be her best match. She’d also do well as an only dog where she would get ALL the attention. She loves people, but can sometimes be a bit shy when meeting them at first. Bailey is now healthy, happy, and full of life! She’s looking for a family to call her own that she can love forever. Do you think our sweet girl would fit in your life? If so, fill out an application to meet Bailey today. 

https://form.jotform.com/91891

animal.description:
***Sable is currently located in Georgia but also available for adoption in NJ and the surrounding areas. If interested in adoption Sable, please submit an application at socorescue.com. (no phone calls please.)***

Sable is a 3 month old Lab/Bulldog mix who came to our rescue as an owner surrender along with her siblings. They previously lived in filth, weren't given proper care and most likely would have perished if they hadn't been rescued.

Sable is a very confident, well socialized little girl. She's smart, friendly and a joy to be around. Sable will make a great family companion and friend for life.

Sable is up to date on her first year vaccinations, has been de-wormed, treated against parasites and started on her monthly preventatives. Sable's' adopter must agree to having her spay once she reaches 6 months of age and provide proof of such to our rescue. She will need all of her basic training.

animal.description:
Purty is 6 years old and weighs 58 lbs.

You must be an approved adopter to VIEW our animals. If you find an animal that you are interested in, please complete an online adoption application. All adoptable animals are first come, first serve, and the application does not guarantee the availability of a specific animal or adoption approval.

Please do not wait for someone to respond to your application submission; if you are interested, visit the shelter to check your application status. All of our animals are FREE to approved adopters and are first come first serve. They will have their annual vaccinations, spayed/neutered, microchipped, and given the first month of Advantage Multi. All Sumter County residents will receive a free County tag for their new family member.
https://www.sumtercountyfl.gov/FormCenter/Animal-Services-12/Adoption-Application-54

You may also come into our facility to complete an adoption application.

WE ARE OPEN EVERY DAY!
KENNEL HOURS TO VIEW ANIMALS:
Monday – Saturday 10:30am -4:00pm
Sunday 11:00am – 3:00pm
NO APPOINTMENT NEEDED!

Please come and visit Sumter County Animal Services to meet your new possible fur-friend

animal.description:
I want to be YOUR boy, Blue! 

I’m a very active 2 year-old, who’s 62 pounds, and a mixed breed. Now I’m truly one of a kind, who’s looking for a Foster to Adopt home! 

I’m a really curious boy, with lots of energy to go explore; but boy is being active great, am I right?!?! I’ve been told I’d make the greatest running partner! Also great news, I’m both potty and crate trained! Now I LOVE toys.. but you know those squeaky things in toys? Yeah.. I hope you don’t like them, because this boy CAN’T have them.. I find them to make me overstimulated and anxious.. but if you don’t like squeakers as much as I can’t have them then great; we’re on the same page! Sometimes I tend to grab a hold of shirt sleeves if I'm feeling unhappy or anxious, and I also tend to be pretty vocal in the car! However, I do love to lean into my humans for some pettings! I’m looking for a home with no other dogs, cats or children. 

Operation Freedom Ride has been so great to me, implementing everything I need to set me up for a promising future! I’m currently in a two week board and training program with a lovely lady named Devan. Devan is focusing on helping me relax and handle boredom situations between training and exercise sessions. Im looking for a home that is willing and most importantly dedicated to continuing my training with Devan, so I can continue succeeding and receive the best possible future I deserve.

I was one of the extra lucky ones this year, as I was a last minute pull from TN! I was meant to be here to find you!!

If you are looking for an “only child”, in which you’ll continue my training with Devan, and give me the patience and time I deserve.. please fill out an application at www.operationfreedomride.com/dog

animal.description:
IMPORTANT: Please do not do an inquiry through Petfinder, our volunteers do not have time to reply to the inquiries. Please visit our website to learn more about our adoption process at newhoperescue.org. 

This dog is being fostered with New Hope Dog Rescue (Saskatoon).  If you are interested in adopting please fill out an Adoption Application. Meet and greets are by appointment only and done so after an adoption application has been submitted. A successful applications will be contacted by the foster home to discuss further. We are volunteer run so please be patient.

Meet Sage. A German shepherd mixed female who is looking for her forever home. When she came to us she was extremely shy and unsure of her surroundings. Since then, she has started opening up to her foster parents and has become friends with the other dogs in the house. Sage loves the outdoors, she would much rather be outside then stuck indoors. She shows affection by giving kisses and wiggles her bum when she is very happy! Sage needs a very patient family that will allow her to open up on her own terms as she is quite shy around new people at first. Sage has a lot of energy and if she doesn’t get the chance to exercise she likes to get into mischief (her foster mom learned this when it was -40 out)! She loves car rides, mingling with other dogs, house & kennel trained and great on the leash. If you want to win her over... a spoonful of peanut butter does the job! 

Sage has been fixed, microchipped, dewormed, current on age appropriate vaccines and has received a health check from a vet. adoption fee is 

To view more dogs go to http://www.newhoperescue.org/adopt/available-dogs/

Disclaimer: in most cases we are guessing the breed mix. These are best guesses on our part. For puppies it can be extremely difficult and we are also guessing on what size they will be. 

NEW HOPE DOG RESCUE is not a shelter. Our dogs are placed in loving foster homes. WE NEED FOSTER HOMES TO HELP MORE DOGS - CONTACT US TODAY!!!
Definitions:
Pending - means that we are working through the adoption process with the 1st applicant. We usually don't add the pending until we are pretty sure the adoption will go through (like at the home visit stage)
Adopted - you know!! A happy ending for a homeless dog.

animal.description:
For auld lang syne, my dear
For auld lang syne
We’ll tak a cup o’ kindness yet
For days of auld lang syne. 

Meet the New Year’s Litter!  Auld, Lang and Syne were surrendered to our rescue after being found in a field. They were emaciated, scared and had skin issues, but they are doing great now. They are looking for their forever homes to start the New Year off right!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are crate trained and are working on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency, patience and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER HOMEPAGE. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Lang
Breed:  Lab mix
Gender:  Male
Age:  7 months
Weight: 30 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Tested Negative 1/15/21, currently on Heartgard 
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our animals are fostered in various locations in the a South and in New England. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers who work full-time jobs and have animals of our own, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description:
Huntley – American Bulldog mix – 5yrs. – male (69 lbs.)

Introducing our handsome big boy, Huntley! Huntley was picked up as a stray on the side of a road by County Animal Control, but luckily he was microchipped. Or so they thought... his owners were called (several times), but they never showed up to pick Huntley up. Poor boy, they didn’t care enough to get him back. Well, no worries sweet boy, we care and we’re going to find you the perfect home! Huntley appears to be housebroken and his favorite thing is to take a blanket, make it just right, and then curl up on it to take a long nap. He’s okay with other dogs, but definitely enjoys the company of people much more. Huntley does well on a leash and loves a long walk. He enjoys every minute of the adventure. He’s athletic and will make a great hiking and camping buddy – can you just see this sweet boy curled up in a sleeping bag next to his person? All Huntley’s looking for is a person/family to love. Could you be that person? If you think so, please fill out an application to get the process started to make our boy your boy. ??

https://form.jotform.com/91891552799173

AC21-54 BONES

Bones came in as a stray. He is approximately a 1.5 year old, male, Labrador mix. He is great with staff and has not been tested with other dogs. At the time it is unknown if Bones is house/crate trained. Dogs are NOT tested with children and cats; his behavior towards children and cats is unknown. He will be available for adoption/rescue on February 09 2021. Additional information is not available, Petfinder bio is up to date. If this is your dog please give the shelter a call right away

Everyone is welcome to adopt from our facility, we like to give the same opportunity to adopt. Adopters can be from out of town and/or local.
*PLEASE CALL ON THE DAY OF AVAILABILITY TO SET AN APPOINTMENT*
You are more than welcome to call us on February 09 2021 to set an appointment to meet him and possibly adopt him that day. It is a FIRST CALL FIRST SERVE. Appointments made before his availability is not available, appointments made by via email is not available. If he is reclaimed by owner before his availability, he will be removed from Petfinder immediately.
----- FIRST CALL FIRST SERVE ---
*Dogs are not adopted out naturally. All dogs will be neutered/spayed once adopted. Depending on the availability of our local vet, it is not a guarantee that the animal will be spayed/neutered the same day*

- Will not accept animal surrenders until further notice

Rescue is a non profit organization with a tax exempt 501(c)(3). If you never pulled from the Wasco Animal Shelter, please email us two references and a copy of your 501(c)(3) form.

*If you have any questions, make sure to give us a call (661)-758-7240*

animal.description: Zeus is a handsome 1 year old 55lb neutered male American Pit Bull Terrier mix. He came into the shelter as a stray, so we do not have any previous background history on him. He is very food motivated, energetic and affectionate here at the shelter. He may thrive best in a home where he is the only dog. He is heartworm negative. We are open by appointment only to ensure we can properly social distance here at the shelter. We cannot guarantee a specific pet or type of pet will be available at your appointment. We do not hold pets. We operate on a first come first serve basis and while you can put what/who you are interested in in the appointment sign up, all appointments are general dog/cat/other animal appointments since we cannot guarantee what will be available at the time of your appointment. If you would like to set up a non-specific dog or cat appointment we have our scheduling system online now at: https://guilfordcountync.gov/our-county/animal-services/animal-shelter/animal-adoption-scheduling All adopted cats and dogs at Guilford County Animal Services come fully up to date on age appropriate vaccines, spayed/neutered, and microchipped. If you are interested in meeting any of our pets, please visit our website to schedule an appointment online. If you believe this may be your pet, please come to the shelter during business hours and bring your ID, proof of ownership, and proof of spay/neuter and/or rabies vaccination history if you have it. See our reclaiming your pet page for more information. If you have any further questions, please contact us at 336-641-3400 or visit our website at https://guilfordcountync.gov/our-county/animal-services/animal-shelter. Thank you for your interest in helping the animals of Guilford County!

animal.description: Looking for a new best friend? Come take a peek at Zeek!! Zeek lived in one home his whole life, and is struggling to understand why he's found himself at the shelter. animal.description: Woof, woof! I'm so excited you're thinking about adopting a new fur-ever family member! Here are a few things that may help you with your big decision. First, dogs just want to be happy and feel loved. Living inside and being a part of the family is really important to us. A lot of the things you need as humans to stay happy and healthy, us dogs need too. We depend on you for things like vet visits, nutritious food, clean water, social and play time with people and other pets, training classes, toys, and of course, lots of love and attention! Regular baths, nail trims and grooming help us to look and feel our best, while monthly flea and heartworm prevention help us to stay healthy. Did you know that depending on our size and breed, dogs can live up to 20 years? Just think of the wonderful life we could have together!

animal.description: Hi, my name is Brad. I'm estimated to be 5 years old and weigh about 75 pounds. I'm a sweet boy, who likes playing with other dogs in playgroups, here at the Shelter. I was returned to the shelter because I'm a fairly large dog and was too much for my previous owners. They also told the shelter that I need work on my potty training and that I need constant supervision. If I get bored I will entertain myself with all the fun indoor things--like furniture. I might have been an outside dog, but I'm not telling. Because I'm a leash puller, I would enjoy taking some obedience classes with my new owner, so I can learn better leash manners. I have a fatty tumor (lipoma) on my front leg and one on my flank, which happens to some of us older guys, but they aren't bothering me and don't need to be removed. For more information or to set up an appointment to meet me, please call the Jackson County Animal Shelter at 541-774-6654. My adoption fee is $150, plus $25 for an annual dog license, if you live in Jackson County.

animal.description:
If you are interested in this dog, don't waste time with an inquiry! Fill out an application here to get the ball rolling...
https://pethavenmn.org/adopt/adoptable-dogs/dog-adoption-application/

Meet: Fae! This 40lb, 7 month old cutie is ALL herding breed and she's seeking an experienced owner! 

Ok, well technically her DNA is not 100% herding breeds... her previous family DNA tested her and she's mostly Australian Cattle Dog, with some Australian Shepherd, Malamute, and American Pit Bull Terrier mixed in. But she possesses many of the qualities of a stereotypical working/herding breed pup! 

Like what, you ask? 

She's one of the smartest dogs you'll ever meet. She loves to run and is very agile for her age. She thrives when she has a job to do. Fae bonds very quickly and completely with "her people". She's high energy. 

She also, though, possesses the quirks that come with these breeds - she is so alert that she is anxious, especially when she isn't mentally and physically drained. Due to this anxiety, she has some stranger danger and needs slow introductions to new people.

Fae thrives within a household where there is structure and order. She previously lived in a household with 3 school aged children and it was just too much chaos for her, so she is seeking a home where there is no regular access to children. Due to her anxious/fearful tendencies, she is seeking an experienced adopter; she would not be a good fit for someone who's ready to adopt their first-ever pup.  Fae does have very mild separation anxiety, as expressed by whining/barking for about 5-10 minutes after you leave, so a home dwelling with shared walls wouldn't be a good fit for her. 

Fae will be headed to her furever home with a lot of smarty-pants tricks under her belt. She's potty trained, crate trained, leash trained and placework trained. She knows "Sit", "Lay Down", "Come" and she is working on "Stay". She is also working on muzzle training and doing great.

Fae has lived with dogs and cats and does well with both. She did like to chase the cats (she's a herding breed dog, what do you expect?!) so if her new home had a cat it would have to be a dog-savvy cat that's able to stand it's ground. She has done great with every dog she's met, but she does resource guard food and high value toys from other dogs in the home so she's seeking an adopter who is comfortable keeping those up/away when multiple dogs are present. 

Fae is such a happy-go-lucky puppy who brings a smile to everyone's face. She may not give her love away for free to just anyone... but once you're in the Fae's Fan Club, you're in for life.,, and trust me, you want to be in! When she sees someone she knows/loves, her floofy tail wags so hard it moves her ENTIRE body! If you want to join the Fae Fan Club and you're an active household who's ready for a high-octane, crazy-smart pup, apply to meet Fae!

Please note: due to Fae's stranger danger, we will be requiring multiple in-person meetings with her prior to adoption. All meetings will follow Covid-safe protocol. 


Her adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm/Lyme test, all age-appropriate vaccinations (distemper, rabies, & Bordetella), HW and flea/tick preventative, and microchip implant and registration.

Adoption fees INCLUDE a mandatory sales tax of 7.525%.

Due to post-adoption services provided, it is Pet Haven's policy to only place dogs into homes within a 75-mile radius of the Minneapolis, MN city center.

animal.description:
For auld lang syne, my dear
For auld lang syne
We’ll tak a cup o’ kindness yet
For days of auld lang syne. 

Meet the New Year’s Litter!  Auld, Lang and Syne were surrendered to our rescue after being found in a field. They were emaciated, scared and had skin issues, but they are doing great now. They are looking for their forever homes to start the New Year off right!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are crate trained and are working on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency, patience and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER HOMEPAGE. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Auld
Breed:  Lab mix
Gender:  Male
Age:  7 months
Weight: 30 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Tested Negative 1/15/21, currently on Heartgard 
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

Brewer – Shepherd mix – 3yrs. – male (40lbs.)

Say hello to our sweetheart, Brewer! He was found as a stray in a Walmart parking lot and picked up by Animal Control. We saw his cute face and had to bring him back with us. Brewer has been doing really well at our shelter! While we don’t know much about his past, we can tell you that he is a happy, bouncy, playful boy who loves people. He does well with women, men, and children... he’s not picky! Brewer believes that everyone should pay attention to him and if you don’t, he’ll make sure to let you know. ? He does well on a leash, but would benefit from some basic training. He doesn’t have accidents in his kennel area so we believe that he is housebroken. Brewer thinks tummy rubs were made for him and his favorite “resting” place is in someone’s lap! He loves to play with other dogs, but can be a bit energetic for some – he likes to play rough and tumble. Brewer is happy, fun-loving, and a joy to have around. He is looking for a home with a good-sized yard to run his energy out and a loving person or family to take care of him forever. If our boy seems like a good fit for your life, please fill out an application to get the process started.

animal.description:
Happy 2021 Folks! My name is Noah and like most of you, I have high hopes for this new year and my greatest hope is for a new home. SEE MY VIDEO! I know sit, stay, rollover, shake and high five!

After being rescued and adopted eight years ago as a young pup, I now find myself homeless again due to Covid. My dad lost his job and couldn’t keep me. It was a sad parting and thankfully, my original rescuer was able to take me back in and is fostering me.
 
First, don’t let my age scare you. I’m healthy, trained, fun-loving and enjoy playing with toys and with my people. I am 75 lbs. My foster mom had me thoroughly checked out at the vet and other than some thinning hair on my back, I received a clean bill of health. I’m crate and house-trained and love going for walks. We take a daily walk through the woods with her dogs and next to eating and cuddling, it’s my favorite activity.
 
Before I was adopted eight years ago, my foster mom took me through a training class. I know shake and sit and if you say “close”, I’ll walk by your side. Treats and praise are very rewarding to me. I’m often told how beautiful I am. I have a unique eye and coat color for a boxer mix. My fur is so soft that it feels like velvet.
I can be a goof ball which makes my foster mom and her daughter laugh. I’m also good with children and especially enjoy playing with older kids. 

I’m fine being an only dog, or I can live with other dogs as long as they are fun-loving or chill female dogs. I don’t mind small dogs or puppies either. I’m just not a fan of dominant dogs or grumpy dogs.  

So, come on folks! What are you waiting for? Let’s make good things happen this year. Let’s become a family and share lots of love, fun and laughs. These are the things that matter. 

If you are interested, please email my Uncle Greg at greg.carraway@yahoo.com. My adoption fee include all my shots, spay, microchip and transport. My adoption fee is $200

animal.description:
Tadpole is a whole lotta puppy! 
Not for the faint of heart or less active, Tadpole will be an excellent 'grown up' dog given the right training and boundaries. This sweet 6 month old Lab/Pyranees mix is a big, floppy, happy go lucky puppy that doesn't quite know how to 'dog' yet- his previous home didn't give him very much structure or direction, and because of that, he would love some obedience training! 

The right home for Tadpole will be active, non-beginner dog owners who understand the importance of obedience training. He would love to go on hikes (once he figures out what he's supposed to do on a leash). He knows how to sit, and is super smart, so we know he has a lot of potential. He loves to fetch and is on his way learning how to 'drop it' and picks up on everything super fast.

If his adopters have children, they will have to be at least 10 - he doesn't quite understand that kids are less sturdy than adults and is definitely a knock-over hazard with his floppy puppy body and enthusiasm. 

When adopted, Tadpole will be neutered, microchipped, UTD on rabies, distemper/parvo, bordatella, and flea/tick/heartworm prevention. He is heartworm negative. Tadpole has lots of love to give, and a lot of joy!

animal.description:
PLEASE READ CAREFULLY 
If you want to adopt go to our website and fill out an application 

safesnout.com



CHALO 
Mixed breed 
26 lbs 
One year old 


Chalo was rescued from the streets in Thailand. Our partnership with SOI DOG FOUNDATION has brought her here to DACHSHUND & FRIENDS SOCIETY a for a chance to have a wonderful life .
Chalo is sweet and loves attention.
Confident in the run, approaches visitors. 
Tentative in some places when walking outside. 
Walks well on a leash. 
Gets on with other dogs.


Chalo was living on the streets of Phuket Island near the Chalong temple – a life filled with danger from other dogs as well as traffic and cruel people. It was a struggle to survive but she managed to get by for the first year of her life. One day Chalonggirl was hit by a car and badly injured, she lay on the side of the road, not moving. Luckily a kind local person saw her and called Soi Dog Foundation for help. An emergency rescue team brought this poor girl to the shelter for the medical treatment she desperately needed. After surgery and rehabilitation Chalo  is doing well. Her sweet personality captivates everyone she meets – both canine and human. Chalo is ready to find her forever family and experience life as a precious pet for the first time.

ADOPTER NEEDS TO BE AWARE  

Chalo will need an area is fully enclosed ( no gaps ) with solid fencing or walling to a minimum height of 6FT to ensure she cannot escape when lose in the area. The area must also be free of any debris, bins, ?or? platforms against the fencing that a dog can jump onto to get over the fence. 
Chalo has been a street dog for much of her life and has never lived inside a  house before, so probably has never climbed stairs, been in a car, slept inside a room with a door shut,  learned to? ?go to toilet ? ?outside, heard ? ?noises from dishwashers, ? ?kettles, ? ?TV’s, ? ?Phones ? ?etc. For ? ?these reasons, you will need to be extremely patient with Chalo to  help her? ?learn how to live in a house and a domestic environment, which can take 6-12 months. 
As Chalo? ?is not yet 2 years of age, she is still considered a puppy, and as such will may behave like one up to approximately 2 years of age. Puppies usually have more energy ?and ?Chalo will need plenty ? ?of regular exercise and play time and safe chew toys so she is not bored .Chalo might bark or cry when left on her own, so adopter will need to be patient and teach Chalo gradually, that being alone is nothing to be scared of. Chalonggirl may need toilet training, and also gentle introductions to things that 
are new to her. Positive training will help her learn all these of things, Once ? ?Chalonggirl?  ?has become familiar with her new home, we highly recommend enrolling her in training class 

Chalo is a family member and at no time will she ever be left outside or be crated unless temporary crating, in case of an emergency situation in which the safety of either Chalo is compromised.?Dachshund & Friends Society believes ?it is detrimental to a dogs physical and mental health to unnecessarily subject a dog to crating h?ealth?.

animal.description:
Taryn – American Staffordshire Terrier/Labrador mix – 2yrs. – male (62 lbs.)

Meet our beautiful little mama, Taryn! This beautiful girl was found wandering in the desert and went right up to the Animal Control Officer when she stopped to pick her up. Once they got her back to the county shelter, they realized that she looked like she had recently had puppies so they took her back to the area where they found her and let her out. She led them straight to her puppies. What a great mom! SHR took her from that county shelter as soon as we could so Taryn and her puppies could live comfortably in our mama foster. Now Taryn is done raising puppies, spayed, and ready to find a home of her own! Although we don’t know much about Taryn’s past, we can say that we believe she was in a home and well taken care of. When she was found, she wasn’t underweight, her coat looked healthy, and she hasn’t had any accidents in her kennel area. We believe she was an inside dog to someone. Not only is she beautiful, she’s so sweet! Sadly, she is not having a good time in the shelter environment. But once she’s out of her kennel, she is loving, affectionate, and craves attention. She does well on a leash and has good manners. We have not had any luck mixing her with other dogs, so we believe her best home would be as an only dog. But what a dog! Taryn will give some lucky person or family all the love, snuggles, and entertainment that they can handle. If you think you may be that “lucky” person, please fill out an application to get the process started.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Brewster is a fluffy little companion blend. He has a great temperament and his coat will require grooming.Ritzy Rescue and Posh Puppy are programs created by CVRR to feature Purebred and Designer dogs. Many of our purebreds are rescued from local puppy mills; some are surrendered by owners who can no longer care for them.
All of our Ritzy and Posh dogs are in need of loving, nurturing homes. Many of them come to us with a serious lack of socialization, malnourished, unvaccinated and desperately in need of grooming and dental care. We place them in foster homes, attend to their physical and emotional needs and begin the process of finding suitable forever homes.
If you are interested in providing a loving home for a Ritzy Rescue or Posh Puppy you must complete an online application at www.cvrr.us
We are only able to respond to interested parties who have completed applications online. Thank you.

Many of our dogs can be seen at Petsmart in Visalia on Saturdays between 10 and 3.

animal.description:
Happy 2021 Folks! My name is Noah and like most of you, I have high hopes for this new year and my greatest hope is for a new home. SEE MY VIDEO! I know sit, stay, rollover, shake and high five!

After being rescued and adopted eight years ago as a young pup, I now find myself homeless again due to Covid. My dad lost his job and couldn’t keep me. It was a sad parting and thankfully, my original rescuer was able to take me back in and is fostering me.
 
First, don’t let my age scare you. I’m healthy, trained, fun-loving and enjoy playing with toys and with my people. I am 75 lbs. My foster mom had me thoroughly checked out at the vet and other than some thinning hair on my back, I received a clean bill of health. I’m crate and house-trained and love going for walks. We take a daily walk through the woods with her dogs and next to eating and cuddling, it’s my favorite activity.
 
Before I was adopted eight years ago, my foster mom took me through a training class. I know shake and sit and if you say “close”, I’ll walk by your side. Treats and praise are very rewarding to me. I’m often told how beautiful I am. I have a unique eye and coat color for a boxer mix. My fur is so soft that it feels like velvet.
I can be a goof ball which makes my foster mom and her daughter laugh. I’m also good with children and especially enjoy playing with older kids. 

I’m fine being an only dog, or I can live with other dogs as long as they are fun-loving or chill female dogs. I don’t mind small dogs or puppies either. I’m just not a fan of dominant dogs or grumpy dogs.  

So, come on folks! What are you waiting for? Let’s make good things happen this year. Let’s become a family and share lots of love, fun and laughs. These are the things that matter. 

If you are interested, please email my Uncle Greg at greg.carraway@yahoo.com. My adoption fee include all my shots, spay, microchip and transport. My adoption fee is $200

animal.description:
AGE: 3 years 6 Months 

BREED: Purebred German Shepherd 

WEIGHT: 88.4 lb

MY STORY:(NOT suitable for an apartment, MUST have a fenced yard)
Zeus is very friendly and a beautiful purebred German Shepherd. He loves playing fetch, knows commands and loves affection! He is truly a magnificent boy deserving of a forever home and loving family. Zeus would do best in a home with no young children and no cats. He is very loyal and loving and does good with other dogs as well. He enjoys chasing snowballs and running out his energy in a fenced yard.  Come meet Zeus today, He is currently accepting adoption applications! 

MORE DETAILS:

This dog must live indoors.

All dogs and puppies at Raccoon River Pet Rescue (RRPR) have been spayed/neutered, have age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped, and treated for fleas, ear mites, and worms.

If you are interested in adopting, please complete an online adoption application at www.RaccoonRiverPetRescue.com and select menu option 'Adoption'. Serious applications only please. Applications will be considered in the order we receive them.

Once an application has been submitted, a member of the RRPR team will contact you usually within 24 hours. Please be patient and thank you for your interest in adopting with us!

Questions? Email us at RRPRmanager@gmail.com or call (515) 465-1800.

animal.description: Hello there, I'm Raven. I am currently staying at HALO with my sister Starfire and we're awaiting our new forever home. We're a bonded pair, which means we must go home together - we rarely separate and are usually found staying close together. If you have other dogs in your home now, we would like to meet them before going home with them, to make sure we're a pawfect fit. While staying in HALO's care, we have enjoyed the company of other dogs alike to our size and it's even helped build up more positive and healthy relationships with other furry friends, so we may indeed like another friendly and social dog companion. We've traveled from Casa Grande to be with our HALO pals and have been working on continued training on building up our confidence as we have been quite timid. We appreciate when humans approach us calmly, slowly and confidently. Our best home would be with adult-humans only (since we can be pretty nervous) and in a house environment, so we have plenty of room to feel comfortable. It may take us some time to warm up to new people after our adoption, but after our acclimation and finding comfort in knowing we're truly home, our true personalities will shine. We look forward to meeting our new family and being the best dogs we can be. If you have room in your heart and home for both myself and Starfire, please contact HALO to make an appointment to meet us.
animal.name: Raven

animal.description: Hello! Let me introduce myself, my name is Stella. I am on the hunt for my furever home. I like to go for daily walks, hikes, bike rides, or runs! I also love to go on adventures and spend time playing with you. My ideal family will have adults only, or if there are children they should be older humans (16+) to take me on explorations and spend time with me. While staying at HALO, I have gotten along with other dogs in my playgroup, so please bring your whole family to meet me, including your current furry friends, to make sure we're a good match, too! I think having another pup in my home would help boost my confidence, too. I've been called high-energy and love to go-go-go, so my best home would be a house with a fenced yard, where I can stretch my legs and exercise when you're busy. I offer a life time of love and devotion. If you have room in your heart and home for a sweet girl like me, please schedule with my HALO friends to meet me. I look forward to knowing you, soon!

animal.description:
Maya is a sweet, silly 1 year old shepherd/beagle mix that is ready to be your new BFF! A perfect 35lbs, Maya is the perfect "medium" sized dog. 

Made of sugar, spice, and everything nice, Maya is past the naughtiest of puppy behaviors, but still acts like a puppy in all the best ways. She loves to play, has never met a stranger, and gets along with cats, dogs and kids - she would fit seamlessly into any family. The whole package! 

Maya is allergic to fleas, so it will be very important for her new family to keep her up to date on flea prevention - but that is her only downfall, if you could even call it that. 

When adopted, Maya will be spayed, microchipped, up to date on rabies, distemper/parvo, and bordatella vaccines. She is heartworm negative and kept current on flea/tick/heartworm prevention.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Hope is a sweet 3 month old puppy who is looking for her forever home! She's a mixed breed - mama is 30 lbs. Hope is one of Holly's puppies that came from Kentucky, and she's one bright little lady, already learning to sit and lay down!

Interested in adopting? Please complete a pre-adoption application at https://redemptionroadrescue.rescuegroups.org/forms/form?formid=4003.

PLEASE NOTE: We expect a high volume of interest in this puppy, so please be patient with us as we review all applications. As a foster-based rescue, we don't have a facility for visits with multiple animals. Meet & greets with dogs are arranged one the pre-adoption application has been received, processed, reviewed, AND approved.

For Puppies adoption fee is $450.00 for the age appropriate vetting they have had so far. (2 DHPP vaccines, deworming on a schedule, and will come with microchip) Puppies still need: 1-2 more DHPP vaccines and a rabies on an age appropriate schedule, and eventual spay or neuter (recommended when closer to 5 1/2- 6 months old) If you want the puppy altered with our vet, the adoption fee is $650.00 (adopter is responsible for the in between vaccines).
