I'm Tramp just looking for my lady( actually my family). I'm a 3 year old, Pomsky(Pomeranian/Husky) and I'm the best of both worlds. I weigh 28#, I love to sit in your lap, and I press into you so I can be as close as possible. I also sing the song of my people when I'm excited or want what you have, my foster parents laugh every time! I'm crate and potty trained, do fantastic with other dogs and I'm okay with cats too. I love love kids and playing! I am fearful of men until I know they won't hurt me, then they are okay too. I'm am also neutered, up to dates on my vaccinations, microchipped and I'm on monthly preventatives!! And drum roll . . . I know how to sit. Whew!! See almost perfect! . No phone calls please.

This dog is fostered in Pratt, KS and adopter must drive to pick up. We do not ship or deliver. We do allow out of state adoptions, however qualified in state applications will be given preference. Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. animal.description:
If you're interested in adopting Billie, please reach out to her foster family at lcp312704@gmail.com. 

Meet Billie! This young pup is looking for to spend all her days with a loving, active, family! 

Billie has shown to be wise beyond her youthfulness - for a 6 month old pup, Billie has already demonstrated to be potty trained in her foster home. While she's still working on getting some tricks down, there is so much time ahead for learning. 

Billie has learned that stairs are not so scary after all, that back yards are for running, toys are for playing, and cars are for rides! Billie's fosters even took her on a hike and added it to her list of favorite ways to spend her days.

Once she gets her energy out, Billie loves to find different spots close to her people to snooze. Billie's current foster parents also tell us that she can be trusted in the house while you're out running errands and loves to greet you with happy kisses as soon as you're back. 

Billie will make a great addition to any family looking to add some love and happiness into their lives!

animal.description:
Hey! I'm King. I'm just over a year old and a ton of fun! I'm microchipped, neutered, up-to-date on shots and ready to find my perfect family! 

I've had a rough start to life, but you wouldn't know it... other needing some help with my manners. I was stuck in a crate 23 hrs a day for my first 9 months and then surrounded to a shelter. Pawsitive Tails bailed me out minutes before euthanasia. After all this, I still think people are great. 

I've been adopted and returned because: I can jump a 4 ft fence, because I like to play so much I annoy my older fur siblings, and because I just need my puppy energy redirected. After getting a lucky break twice, I deserve a great home that will be patient with me and teach me how to be the good boy I want to be! I really want to find my forever person that will love me while I learn. 

Here are the reasons I'm so awesome * I'm super smart, I know sit, high five, lay down, and I'm learning off and leave it * house and kennel trained *I LOVE to play * a great co-pilot in the car * walk well on a leash * love water (playing in the hose is my favorite!) 

I am up to date on vaccines, dewormed, heartworm negative, current on preventatives, neutered and microchipped! My adoption fee is $150. To meet me, just fill out an application at www.pawsitivetailskc.org and my foster will be in touch!

animal.description:
This puppy is in Tennessee. Adoption Donation $250 if picked up in TN, $300 plus transport fee for out of state adoptions.

Fantastic, fun-loving and feisty gal Cricket is as sweet and as smart as she can be! She's a 8-month-old, 20 pound Beagle mix, with lots of love to give and energy to share. Cricket is a happy girl, always eager to please and looking for an activity to participate in. She is an athletic pup who needs LOTS of mental and physical exercise in her new home. Her favorite hobbies including running, jumping, and chasing her foster dog siblings. Cricket is good with the cat in her foster home too, and would also enjoy some dog-savvy kids to keep her occupied. She is a quick learner, highly treat motivated, and is already working on her training with her foster family. Cricket is eager to learn more new things in her forever home, like basic obedience, tricks and more. She has basically already mastered the art of housetraining - she knows to ring a bell to go out! Cricket is crate trained also. She is a cuddle bug at the end of a long day of play, so snuggling on the couch is another one of her pastimes. Busy is this gals middle name, so be sure you are ready for lots of adventures with Cricket! She is a ninja of an escape artist, so a securely fenced yard or dedicated leash exercise is needed. Cricket requires someone willing to work with her on training and maybe even let her burn off some energy doing Agility. If you think you're up for the challenge, apply to adopt today!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: http://aarf-tn.com/adopt/adoption-apps/

If you have questions that are not covered in the profile, visit the Pet Inquiry Form: http://aarf-tn.com/contact/pet-inquiry-form/.

THIS PET IS FOSTERED IN TENNESSEE! We do list and adopt our pets nationwide. Typical transport cost to the Northeast is $160. Due to interstate adoption regulations, we are not able to adopt to RI and MA state residents.

A.A.R.F. (All About Rescue and Fixin' Inc.) http://aarf-tn.com/ is a non-profit, 501(c)(3) no kill animal rescue organization located in the Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee. A.A.R.F. is comprised of unpaid volunteers and survives only on public donations. Thank you for thinking adoption first!

Prior to adoption, all canines and felines are spayed or neutered, have received their age appropriate vaccinations, have been de-wormed for common parasites, and have received treatment for prevention of fleas and ticks. All canines over the age of 6 months have been tested for heartworm. All canines are put on heartworm prevention as soon as possible - this means dogs as soon as they are tested negative. Puppies are put on prevention immediately. All felines, regardless of age, have been tested for Feline Leukemia/FIV. Each animal receives a health check by a licensed veterinarian prior to adoption. Anything else found will be treated by our organization prior to adoption.

animal.description:
Meet Winter!
She's the sweetest girl ever! She would like nothing more than to lay in your lap, she is a complete cuddle bug.
She loves long walks, going on adventures, and men, she just adores them! Small kids make her nervous and she may let out a warning growl if the get too close too soon. She loves little dogs but with larger dogs she becomes dominant.  She is a chewer, so TV remotes should be kept out of reach, she is also learning that corners of furniture is not for chewing. Her foster family has tricked her with some icky tasting stuff on there and that has kept her away. Winter can be a bit shy and timid at first, but once she warms up to you she acts like a big puppy. She is potty trained, but if it is raining outside she would rather not go out (welcome to the PNW). She also does well in her crate at night and when people are gone.
This sweet love bug will need an experienced hooman that can help her with her dominance towards larger dogs and some of her fears. She would love a chill environment with someone who likes to go on adventures. Is it you?! 

PLEASE READ COMPLETELY 

All of our moms are being raised in volunteer foster homes, so we do not have a single location to visit. You will need to submit an application to be approved for a Meet and Greet.

If you are interested in adopting or more information please do the following before contacting Path of Hope: 

1. Go to our website www.pathofhoperescue.com 
2. Thoroughly read through the FAQ section on the "Adopt" page (this will answer most questions!)
3. If you are still interested, fill out an online application on our website and our Matchmaker will be in touch with you! 
4. Follow us on facebook, https://www.facebook.com/pathofhoperescue/ , to see lots of cute puppie photos. learn about puppy events, and get updates on the rescue!

Our adoption fee for mom dogs is $300 and includes age appropriate core vaccines, minimum two rounds of dewormer, microchip with free registration and spay/neuter surgery. A refund of $100 is available with completion of any training class.

animal.description:
Age: 3yrs
Weight: 50lbs
Gender: Male
Energy Level: Moderate to High
Overall Drive: Moderate to High
Location: Eugene, OR
NO YOUNG CHILDREN, CATS OR SMALL ANIMALS

Ruvo is the perfect flexible canine partner that will be a great match for someone who is up for a new adventure each day! Whether you want a lazy day around the house or an action-filled excursion, Ruvo won’t be far from your side.

Ruvo is extremely sweet and affectionate. When in the home, he loves to cuddle but once it’s time to play he is full of energy! He has instantly loved every person he’s met and has been good with children if they respect his space. Ruvo has been good with other dogs with slow, proper introduction. He can be pushy with other dogs but takes corrections well. Due to his high prey drive, Ruvo will need a home without very young children, cats, or small pets. He rides well in the car, is neutral around loud noises, and is fully crate trained. Ruvo is very sensitive to correction and a verbal correction is usually all that is necessary. He has mostly mastered basic obedience and is working on more advanced commands and reducing pulling when on leash.

Ruvo would do well in either a busy or calm home. However, he does enjoy being active so would do best with someone willing to ensure he gets plenty of exercise each day. He’s always up for playing ball, frisbee, or going out for walks or hikes. Ruvo is relatively easy going but will need a somewhat experienced handler to help him through some of his eccentricities. He would do well with a large, neutral male or a large female dog but will need supervision and slow introductions. Ruvo is ready to walk right beside you through whatever life might throw your way – he is the perfect pal!

WEST COAST ADOPTIONS ONLY

Must have previous or current, purebred Malinois experience OR other high drive working breed experience

Our adoption process includes- completion of an application, followed by a telephone interview. If that goes well, we will arrange for a home visit.
Adoption Fee: $500.00. Transport along Interstate 5 (Bakersfield, CA to Bellingham, WA) is available but cost not included in adoption fee. 

Please visit www.woofproject.org and fill out an adoption application located here https://www.woofproject.org/application

animal.description:
****The website is updated several times daily. Please do not email to ask if there are still dogs/puppies available.****

PLEASE READ CAREFULLY!

YOU WILL FIND THE ANSWER TO ALL BASIC QUESTIONS BELOW. Please read carefully Before emailing.

Hank is a 10-11 month old mixed breed guy. He seems to be some variety of bird dog like Beagle, Pointer or Springer, or a few mixes together. It’s hard to say exactly what he is! While he does not bay, he does sing along with sirens! 

Hank is 45 pounds and approx 13-14 inches at the shoulder.  He stands knee high on a 5’7” person. He is happy and wiggly and wants to be loved! 

Hank is very sweet with plenty of energy. He will be a great friend for someone looking to get into training. Obedience, agility, or other dog sports are going to be a must for this guy. (He has never been exposed to any sort of hunting or retrieving.) He looks to his person for guidance and wants to be praised. 

Hank is good with other dogs. He is doing great on house and crate training. He recently had a sleepover at an apartment and did great there too.  He has never lived with cats and may be too much for them. He has not lived with kids younger than middle school age. He is very much a puppy and should be just fine introduced to kids. Hank will need a physically fenced yard or someone dedicated to leash walking. No electronic fences/collars. 

*Each pup is spayed or neutered and current on their vet cares. 

*We do not hold or reserve dogs. We do not ship or fly. Prospective families must come to NORTHFIELD MN to meet.*

*Emails are answered in the order they are received. We are receiving a large number of emails, so answering promptly is our goal. If you are interested in adoption, your prompt responses are the best way to get through the adoption screening*

*Paws First does not accept checks or credit cards. WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO DENY ADOPTIONS AT ANY POINT IN THE ADOPTION SCREENING PROCESS.*

If you have read this far, you are ready to start the adoption process! Please email to get started.

animal.description:
Introducing London! If you're looking for a compact love machine, London is your gal! This beautiful and sweet pitty is around 3 years old and roughly 50 pounds of pure snuggle! London has been staying with a foster family the last couple weeks while we prepare to get her spayed, and they have been sending glowing reviews about how lovely London is as a house guest! 

London's past is a bit blurry, but we know she'll benefit from an adopter that can continue her leash training and provide ample toys to play with! We are not sure how London will do with other pets or children, but she hasn't met an adult that she doesn't absolutely bond with instantly!

All of our animals are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and up to date on age-appropriate vaccinations. If you have any additional questions, or would like to adopt London, please send us an email at resilientheartsanimalsanctuary@gmail.com and we will send you an adopter survey. WE DO NOT RESPOND TO PETFINDER INQUIRIES, ONLY EMAILS.

Resilient Hearts is a 501(c)3 nonprofit animal rescue in Seattle, WA. 100% of adoption fees go towards helping us save more high-risk animals, and unite them with their forever families in the PNW! If you would like to learn more about us, please visit resilientheartsanimalsanctuary.org!

animal.description:
Age: 8yrs
Gender: Female
Weight: 70lb
Energy level: Moderate
Overall drive: Moderate
Location: Bellingham, WA
NO KIDS OR SMALL ANIMALS

Lucy is ready to give love and accept love back! Affectionate and sweet, she will sit next to you to be pet for as long and as often as you’d like. Lucy is loyal, will keep guard over your household, and is always up for playing outside or going for leisurely walks. If she were a human, she’d be a bodyguard who is both concerned with protecting you but also your constant companion.

Lucy has done well with other dogs with proper introductions and as long as their play style remains polite. She is unfazed by other dogs when out on- or off-leash and mostly wants to do her own thing. As for dogs who share her home, Lucy would do best with a non-dominant male playmate. When inside the home, Lucy loves being with her person but also likes having her own space when she requires it. She loves chasing, thus will need a home without cats, small animals, or young children. Lucy has done well meeting people inside her home and is eager to greet them. She has done well at the veterinarian’s office, is calm around loud noises, and has fully mastered basic obedience. Lucy has good house manners and is easily motivated with food. She is eager to please and happy just to be with you and receive all the affection you might wish to offer.

Lucy’s ideal home would be one that has an open spot on the couch for a lovable companion with people who would be willing to give her as much affection as possible. She does enjoy running and playing and would do well with a large, fenced yard. However, she does well on-leash and would also be a good match for someone looking for a walking or hiking partner. Lucy is ready to give all of herself to whoever might be ready to receive it – all you need is love!

WEST COAST ADOPTIONS ONLY

Must have previous or current, purebred Malinois experience OR other high drive working breed experience

Our adoption process includes- completion of an application, followed by a telephone interview. If that goes well, we will arrange for a home visit.
Adoption Fee: $500.00. Transport along Interstate 5 (Bakersfield, CA to Bellingham, WA) is available but cost not included in adoption fee.

animal.description:
Meet Maribel! 

Our blue eyed beauty has been searching for her forever home for almost 7 months and we can’t believe she hasn’t been swooped up yet! Maribel is a 2 year old pit/boxer mix who weighs approximately 55 lbs. She is spayed, up to date on vaccines, and fully vetted. Maribel is also crate and house trained! 

Maribel is a volunteer favorite in our rescue because of her sweet and fun spirit! Maribel is an AMAZING dog and we have no doubt she will make a wonderful addition to your family. Maribel loves all people, including kids, and is just truly a lover at heart. Maribel is the perfect mix of energetic and lazy. She loves her couch snuggles but is also excited to go for an outdoor adventure with you. Honestly if her person is with her Maribel is as happy as can be! Maribel is a true nurturer who loves to take care of her people. If you’re sick Maribel is right by your side providing you comfort and love. If you’ve had a bad day Maribel is there to put a smile on your face and give you kisses. She truly is the perfect girl! 

Maribel does well with other dogs but will need slow introductions to any other pets. She loves her furry foster sister and LOVES LOVES LOVES to play with her! We are happy to talk further about how she would integrate into your home and provide potential adopters with any resources and help we can! 

If you’re interested in adopting Maribel fill out our adoption application at the link below 
www.bullluvablepaws.org/adopt

animal.description:
***All applications will be considered before inquiries as we do not currently have the staff to respond to every inquiry submitted. 

Please meet Sangria’s babies!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are working on crate training and on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They are young and will need supervision and lots of patience. They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PIC OF THE DOG. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Chablis
Breed:  Collie/Lab mix
Gender:  Female
Age:  3 months
Weight: 15 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Too Young
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down or get under their feet. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

Axel is a  GSD mix puppy, 4 months old, about 29 lbs. Just rescued with his siblings, we don't yet know much about him. But isn't it obvious this sweetheart is ready for a forever home and heart!

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for puppies covers initial deworming,  puppy vaccinations, microchip, and spay/neuter at the rescue's approved vet at 6 months of age. Please see our website for more information.

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
Hi there! Jeffrey is looking for a foster home! He is currently 7 weeks old. He will grow to be 80lbs+ and is a large breed mix. We are currently running an Embark DNA test to see what he's mixed with. However, because so many fosters end up adopting their foster dogs, we will need fosters that actually qualify for adoption just in case (we would hate to deny a foster the ability to adopt based on our requirements). So please only apply to foster if you absolutely meet all requirements.

To apply to foster: www.friendsforliferescuenetwork.com/foster

Requirements:
Own your own home- You, the applicant, must be the owner of the home. NO renters. No condos without yards.

Fenced in yard- must be fully fenced

Live locally- Within 20-30 minutes of West Los Angeles due to veterinary care requirements.

Have your own vehicle. We require fosters to travel back to West LA every few weeks for vaccines, etc.

No restrictions on your homeowners insurance based on breed of dog.

Experience with large bully breeds is a plus. Having another dog in the home is a plus.

Meet MARLO
-Male
-2 years old
-Mountain Cur MIX

Marlo is:
-Dedicated
-Adventurous
-Kind
-Active
-Smart
-Energetic
-Loving
-Potty Trained
-House Trained
-Good with submissive dogs
-Good with OLDER children (15+)
-NO CATS!!!!

If you are looking for a loyal companion who will be by you every step of the way, MARLO IS THE PUP FOR YOU!

He is a high drive pup who needs mental and physical stimulation to make his days whole. He will need time to adjust, but once he is comfortable you will have all his attention.He gets bored quick and needs someone to match his energy! He has a BIG heart and aims to please his humans. He gets SO excited to be with his people where at times he may get a little rambunctious. But don’t worry that’s just his animated personality!He loves play time but will never pass up on some belly rubs!! 

Marlo is as smart as they come! He knows basic commands but will need someone who WILL continue with his training!
?Once adopted, Marlo has someone who WILL PAY FOR HIS TRAINING WITH LORENZO TRAINING GROUP!??

After being constantly looked over at the shelter, Marlo grew frustrated and unwanted. This resulted in anger and a spot on the euthanasia list. Amazing volunteers saved him from this life. He is currently in training learning how to socialize and trust again.
Step by step and paw by paw, Marlo is learning how to be a dog again?
Marlo is simply looking for someone to give him a second chance at love??

To read his story please visit this Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/Hope-For-Marlo-102251291791995/

Marlo would shine best with:
-Active Family
-Home with FENCED IN YARD
-Someone dedicated & willing to take him to his training
-Someone with patience 
-Home with NO CATS

If you believe MARLO could be your fuuurever buddy, please fill out an adoption application: https://form.jotform.com/93263081961156

IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS PLEASE EMAIL INFO@MERCYFULLPROJECTS.ORG

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Thorston
DOB: 7/1/2020
Weight: 50lbs
Adoption Fee: $450

Hi! I'm Thor and I think I'm a lap dog. I currently am living with two other pups and after slow introductions we get along great. I don't really realize how big I am and can play a little rough sometimes but if you put me in my place, I will be your best friend. I am fully potty trained and even ring the bell when I need to go outside. If you put my harness and leash on, I know that it is time for a walk which I really enjoy; however, I'm still learning how to be a good walking companion. I like to get some good exercise or play time multiple times a day so would prefer to be with a pretty active family. If I get my exercise, I am just a big, lazy bum who likes to cuddle on the couch.

If you have questions or are interested in me, please fill out an adoption application at www.ruffstartrescue.org.

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal. Please check out our website, www.ruffstartrescue.org for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals! All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs). Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept. Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Age: ~3yrs
Gender: Male
Weight: 62lbs
Energy Level: Moderate
Overall Drive: Moderate
Location: Pleasant Grove, UT

George is a devoted, loving, and fun boy who looks like he always has his eyeliner perfectly applied! If he were a human, he’d be a gymnast – limber, focused, and always wanting to do his best.  George is eager to please and will always offer his best efforts when his person asks for it.

George is very connected with his handler and will check in with them to make sure they are nearby, both in and out of the home. He is curious and loves to explore, especially using his nose to guide him. When George first meets new dogs, his first instinct is to be protective, however he will calm with reassurance from his person and will make friends. He has been friendly to humans who are unknown to him, but his size and exuberance makes him a bit much for small children to handle. George rides well in the car, doesn’t mind loud noises, and doesn’t tend toward destructive behavior. He has been known to scale fences and ladders, and thus a home with a secure fence and someone willing to always monitor him when he is outside of his home is required. George is working on basic obedience and is fully crate trained.

George would love to be a part of an active family where he could have plenty of opportunity to get his energy out each day. He would love having another dog he could play with, and likely would warm up to any dogs he shares his household with once there has been time made for proper introduction. George would likely make a great agility or scent work partner if his new handler is interested. This silly bundle of energy can’t wait to keep a smile on your face in 2021 – start the new year with your new best friend!

WEST COAST ADOPTIONS ONLY

Must have previous or current, purebred Malinois experience OR other high drive working breed experience

Our adoption process includes- completion of an application, followed by a telephone interview. If that goes well, we will arrange for a home visit.
Adoption Fee: $500.00. Transport along Interstate 5 (Bakersfield, CA to Bellingham, WA) is available but cost not included in adoption fee. 

Please visit www.woofproject.org and fill out an adoption application located here https://www.woofproject.org/application

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Cira is my name and playing is my game!! I am approximately 2 yrs old 10lb Cocker/Chi mix possible terrier too.

Cira had been on the streets for a while. We don't really know her past but we do know it was not pleasant due to her issues. Upon capture she did bite an AC officer and was placed on bite protocol. This was because she was in extreme fear. When Cira was at the shelter he was not happy pup snapping at everyone.

We were able to get her and have been working with her and she has come along way. Cira does need some training, her hearing is little bit selective unless a treat is involved. She loves to jump in her foster dads lap and cuddle, with her foster mom Cira is slowly coming around.

Cira is looking for someone who might have another dog for her to play with and to help with her trust issues. A fenced house is required cause she likes to run and play. We are also looking for someone who is home more often than not. She does not like being far from her person.

Patience is the key with her as she has a dramatic start in life. So Cira needs to be a dog again and learn to trust again. So if you have the patience to help her through her issues she would be a great dog!!!! To find out more about Cira fill out and application at www.FureverHomeRescue.Dog

animal.description:
Hi there! Sullivan is looking for a foster home! He is currently 7 weeks old. He will grow to be 80lbs+ and is a large breed mix. We are currently running an Embark DNA test to see what he's mixed with. However, because so many fosters end up adopting their foster dogs, we will need fosters that actually qualify for adoption just in case (we would hate to deny a foster the ability to adopt based on our requirements). So please only apply to foster if you absolutely meet all requirements.

To apply to foster: www.friendsforliferescuenetwork.com/foster

Requirements:
Own your own home- You, the applicant, must be the owner of the home. NO renters. No condos without yards.

Fenced in yard- must be fully fenced

Live locally- Within 20-30 minutes of West Los Angeles due to veterinary care requirements.

Have your own vehicle. We require fosters to travel back to West LA every few weeks for vaccines, etc.

No restrictions on your homeowners insurance based on breed of dog.

Experience with large bully breeds is a plus. Having another dog in the home is a plus.

animal.description:
My name is Zoë, and I come with my best friend Indi. We are inseparable. Let me tell you why: We were saved from a puppy mill where we were used for profit our entire lives. Our rescuer took care of us, taught us how to potty on grass (we didn’t even know what was grass until she showed us) and how to walk on leashes. Before we were rescued, we were locked up in cages and had to eat urine-soaked kibble. We were so emaciated that our ribs and spine were showing! We didn’t even have names! Our rescuer fed us really good food that made us gain weight. We definitely love eating good food! She gave us love and made us feel safe. Before being rescued, we didn’t even know what was a kind human touch. When we go to our forever home, we MUST go together. I cannot live without the other pup and will find a way to escape to be with her since she’s family. We would like to go to a home where we have a big backyard, good food, a warm bed, daily walks, and loving parents. Someone who will care for us our entire lives, no matter how old we get. We are the most loyal pups and love to go for walks and play.

Please, NO homes with small kids or teens. Their scooters and toys scare us and sadly, some kids have been very rough when handling us and have dropped us before. We’ve been used for profit and neglected our entire lives and deserve a loving home where we can give our family lots of kisses and grow old with them.

If you are interested in meeting Zoë & Indi, please download the Adoption Questionnaire (farescue.org/pdf_files/questionnaire_canine.pdf), fill it out and email it back to us at info@farescue.org or fax (310) 362-0321. You can also meet this and/or other available dogs at our weekend adoptions.

[Zoë is 3 years old and weighs 8 lbs.]

animal.description:
***All applications will be considered before inquiries as we do not currently have the staff to respond to every inquiry submitted. 

Please meet Sangria’s babies!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are working on crate training and on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They are young and will need supervision and lots of patience. They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PIC OF THE DOG. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:   Julep
Breed:  Collie/Lab mix
Gender:  Female
Age:  3 months
Weight: 15 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Too Young
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down or get under their feet. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. animal.description:
Ghirardelli is a 9-10 year old chocolate lab. He gets along with dogs of all sizes and ages, but vastly prefers dogs that aren't overly playful or in your face. He is also fine with cats and wonderful with kids. He is housetrained, crate trained, and will use a dog door happily. He's an all around great family dog who wants nothing more than a soft blanket at your feet to lay beside you. He has no separation anxiety, doesn't like being on furniture, and is super independent! I'm telling you, this boy is a jackpot. 
Just one small catch, Ghirardelli needs a quiet home with minimal traffic in and out because his right back leg and hip are damaged beyond repair unfortunately. What does this mean for our handsome friend? Well it means that he has a limp and he needs pain management. Currently he is in 75mg of carprofen and 300mg of gabapentin twice per day. And that he lazes about a little more than your average happy labby. That's it! That's all! His bloodwork was otherwise perfect and his teeth look great. And get this! The old guy even still loves to talk short walks and play the occasional game of tug. 
Ghirardelli is a great dude and he will be available for adoption soon!

animal.description:
My name is Indi, and I come with my best friend Zoë. We are inseparable. Let me tell you why: We were saved from a puppy mill where we were used for profit our entire lives. Our rescuer took care of us, taught us how to potty on grass (we didn’t even know what was grass until she showed us) and how to walk on leashes. Before we were rescued, we were locked up in cages and had to eat urine-soaked kibble. We were so emaciated that our ribs and spine were showing! We didn’t even have names! Our rescuer fed us really good food that made us gain weight. We definitely love eating good food! She gave us love and made us feel safe. Before being rescued, we didn’t even know what was a kind human touch. When we go to our forever home, we MUST go together. I cannot live without the other pup and will find a way to escape to be with her since she’s family. We would like to go to a home where we have a big backyard, good food, a warm bed, daily walks, and loving parents. Someone who will care for us our entire lives, no matter how old we get. We are the most loyal pups and love to go for walks and play.

Please, NO homes with small kids or teens. Their scooters and toys scare us and sadly, some kids have been very rough when handling us and have dropped us before. We’ve been used for profit and neglected our entire lives and deserve a loving home where we can give our family lots of kisses and grow old with them

If you are interested in meeting Indi & Zoë, please download the Adoption Questionnaire (farescue.org/pdf_files/questionnaire_canine.pdf), fill it out and email it back to us at info@farescue.org or fax (310) 362-0321. You can also meet this and/or other available dogs at our weekend adoptions.

[Indi is 1 year old and weighs 15 lbs.]

(2102)

Sweet Older Senior Seeks Companion:  Amell is an older Chihuahua who is searching for his forever home. He is guess-timated to be 10-13 years old. This sassy senior is looking for a quite home where he can spend all of his time with his very own person.  His ideal day is spent sitting on his foster moms lap while she works from home or cuddled in his own bed under her desk.

Amell would do best in an home where he is the only pet.  But he could be happy in a home with children over 13 and other independent animals. He does not like high energy animals that will be in his face (or humans for that matter).  

'Mel needs a family who understands the Chihuahua breed; he's a simple guy who does not like loud noises and will be sure to let you know if things are getting too loud.

Potty training is going great, although he will have accidents if left unattended or not let out on a schedule.

If you have a quiet lap, couch or beds & have been looking for a guy that only has eyes for you then apply to meet Amell today!

animal.description:
Meet Loki, an adorable 6 year old, 7 pound Yorkie boy being fostered in Laguna Hills CA. Due to COVID, no applicants residing outside California will be considered.

Loki is a 6 year old male yorkie.  He weighs about 7lbs.  His previous family had to make the hard decision to find him a new home because they have a very active 3 year old son and a new baby on the way.  Loki was getting very anxious with all the activities and noise that goes along with a toddler.  Loki is a sweet little yorkie boy that has been well loved and cared for.  He loves playing with his little squeaky toys and small squeaky tennis balls.  He is great at fetching and bringing it back, and he can play for a long time.  He is doing well with going potty on the potty pads and also going outside.  He is very smart and even knows how to sit and shake.  He has even learned how to use the doggy stairs for the couch and the bed. He gets along with his foster siblings and knows how to share toys.  He walks well on the leash with his harness.  He does have a lot of energy and will pull in the beginning.   He knows his name and loves his picture taken. He loves going for car rides and even did well at Petsmart with other dogs walking by.  His foster mom had to go to work and as soon as she picked up her car keys he got anxious and started spinning in circles and barking.  According to his foster dad, he settled down quickly and went to snuggle on his foster grandmas lap.  He has his wellness check at the vet on Wednesday Feb 3.

animal.description:
***All applications will be considered before inquiries as we do not currently have the staff to respond to every inquiry submitted. 

Please meet Sangria’s babies!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are working on crate training and on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They are young and will need supervision and lots of patience. They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PIC OF THE DOG. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:   Pinot
Breed:  Collie/Lab mix
Gender:  Male
Age:  3 months
Weight: 15 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Too Young
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down or get under their feet. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description: Elmer is a fun, sweet boy who is extremely smart and loves learning new tricks. He knows sit, stay, off, lay down, out, and paw. He walks nicely on a leash and sits for treats and toys. Elmer still acts like a puppy with lots of playful energy. He is a problem solver and will try to figure out a way to open doors and containers to get what he wants. He’d be great at puzzles or agility training or just as a running and hiking buddy. Elmer can jump very high and will do so to get to things he wants, so he has to be watched outdoors even with a fenced yard. He loves being with people and will choose his person over other things around him. Elmer is crate and house trained and will sleep until you get up every morning, keep you laughing all day, and is the best to snuggle at night. He would do well in a home with another playful and/or tolerant dog his size. Our adoption fee is $300 and we adopt to a 2.5 hour radius of zip code 21034. For more information about any of our wonderful dogs please visit our website at www.blackdogsandcompanyrescue.org or email us at rescueblackdogs@yahoo.com.

animal.description:
Lovely
Female 
Maltese Mix 
10 1/2 Years 
13 lbs 

My name is lovely and my mom died, and her family couldn’t keep me. I’m thankful that New Hope took me in so I did not have to go to a shelter.   

Please understand I was originally rescued from an abused home so I am afraid of loud noises and while I’m very sweet, I can be skittish.  I love snuggling next to you on the couch or in your lap. I love giving small kisses and sleeping on your chest. 

My foster mom says I prance around the yard and that I seem potty trained.  I like to find small places to feel safe, like a laundry basket, but I don’t really enjoy crates.  I avoid dog beds, opting for human pillows instead.  

I co-exist fine with other dogs peacefully but I’m also not super interested in them, so I’m probably not a playmate for other pups in your house.  However,  attention from other dogs doesn’t seem to bother me.  My foster has not heard me growl at all.   

I like to stay near my human and will keep you company while you are gardening or cleaning the house. I’m always curious what you are up to!  

My foster describes me as a chill, calm dog.  I’m not super interested in toys or treats but I do love belly rubs!   I'm affectionate, sweet and just need to feel safe.

animal.description:
Foster location:  Boise ID
Breed:  Fox Terrier Mix
Age:  8(ish) years old
Adoption Fee:  $150.00
Neutered, Vaccinated, Microchipped

If interested you MUST complete the Adoption Application:  http://fuzzypawzrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application-2/
Murphy came to Fuzzy Pawz Rescue as a medical case after finding himself in a local shelter as a stray. Murphy was covered in lumps and bumps and some were pretty concerning looking. 
Fuzzy Pawz Rescue was able to get him medically evaluated and have his bumps removed and had a much-needed dental/tooth extraction. The good news is that all of his blood work came back great and he is a pretty healthy old man. The bad news is that some of his bumps did come back cancerous. The veterinarian and rescue are both hopeful that the cancer was removed during his surgery, but there is always a chance that re-growth could happen in the future and should be looked for. 
Murphy is incredibly sweet and affectionate and likes to be in constant physical contact with the people in his life. Murphy would do best in a home that would allow him lots of snuggle time, access to furniture that people are on and someone who won't mind a Fox Terrier shaped shadow trotting behind them at all times. 
Murphy is pretty relaxed and low energy and doesn’t need energy management, but does enjoy playing with toys and running around. Playing a couple rounds of fetch while out to potty or bonding with his owner on a relaxing walk would be a great fit for him. 
Murphy has many breed traits that Fox Terriers are known for. First, he has the notable tooth chatter that Fox Terrier lovers know well. When he is excited, over stimulated or engaged in chase/play he will start his tooth chatter/ excitement chomps. Additionally, he has a fairly high prey drive that this breed is known and often bred for. Murphy should not be trusted with smaller animals as he has a high prey drive. This includes chickens, turkeys, ducks, squirrels, rabbits, birds and any other prey he thinks he can manage to catch. He should not be adopted to a home with cats. 
As you can see from his photos Murphy loves other dogs and if not snuggled with is human you can find him snuggled up to one of the other dogs in his foster.  He would love to be adopted to a home with another easy going dog but Murphy has some resource guarding tendencies. If there is another dog in the home Murphy will need to be fed separately than other dogs, and does well eating in a crate. Murphy can get snippy with some toys but does not guard during active play. Being well managed is essential to set both Murphy, his new owners and any canine friends up for success. Murphy responds well to verbal correction and praise and can be verbally told to stop a behavior.
Murphy has nothing but love and affection to give and would love to spend his years snuggling with his people. If you are interested in Murphy, please fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
Scooter is an adorable 6 mos old purebred Boston Terrier. He is DEAF. But it doesn’t slow him down a bit. He loves to play and especially likes squeaky toys even though he can’t hear them squeak. He gets along great with other dogs and kids. He would do best in a home that has a young dog for him to play with and be his life partner. He would also love to have kids to play with. 
Scooter is not a fan of being crated in the house so housebreaking will require some effort. He is used to going outside to potty. He might do better in a big crate with his friend. He doesn’t mind being crated for car rides and does very well in the car. Scooter is 18 lbs so a nice size to take along wherever you go. 
He needs a fenced yard and a family that spends a lot of time at home or can take him with them. Also a K9 friend would be best. He’s a super sweet boy and loves to give kisses. 
Scooter has been neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, Heartworm tested negative and current on HW meds. If you are interested in adding Scooter to your family plz contact Ginger for an adoption application. His adoption fee is $600. Located in Central MO.

animal.description:
Meet Abigail the “marshmallow”!
This dog comes with the guarantee that you’ll fall in love in under 60 seconds… the proof is in every single person who has met her. She is an ABSOLUTE sweetheart and it makes our blood boil knowing that up until two weeks ago she lived in a crappy aluminum shed, in squalor, in a city backyard. Thank God for our good friends at Animal Services who work as hard as they do and who brought this girl to our attention. WE ARE IN LOVE. Abigail is approx. 2 – 3 years old and has clearly been bred in the past. This Cane Corso x Boxer has a HUGE personality (in contrast to her stocky body lol), is a gorgeous grey colour with giant white “baseball mitts” for paws, eyes that melt your heart, and a personality that matches.  It was concluded this morning after X-rays and a physical examination by our veterinarian, that Abigail will require a surgery to repair her torn cruciate ligament. For us to ensure she gets the care she needs; she will not be ready to be adopted until after her surgery (in April), but we are currently accepting adoption applications.  Abigail has lived her whole life alone in a backyard, and though she desperately wants to be every dog’s friend, she unfortunately lacks some social graces and does not yet understand appropriate play style. Due to this, currently, she is best suited as the only pet in the house. She has an absolutely wonderful personality, however, is incredibly strong and is still learning basic commands and leash skills. Therefore, a family where all members of the home are over the age of 16 is required. We are looking for a family who have “bully breed” experience who will be on board with attending positive reinforcement training classes to help her further blossom.  For more information on Abigail, email info@thedogrescuersinc.ca

animal.description:
***All applications will be considered before inquiries as we do not currently have the staff to respond to every inquiry submitted. 

Please meet Sangria’s babies!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are working on crate training and on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They are young and will need supervision and lots of patience. They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PIC OF THE DOG. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:   Brunello
Breed:  Collie/Lab mix
Gender:  Male
Age:  3 months
Weight: 15 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Too Young
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down or get under their feet. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

We think he will be fine with children that are respectful and not rough as he is a fragile little guy.

animal.description:
Meet Hope!

Hope is a super sweet pup who isn't afraid to do anything, she is paralyzed in her hind legs but she doesn't let that stop her from doing anything! She loves going on walks and hikes on her wheels, but she also loves lounging in her bed watching tv. She was run over by a car in texas and was dragging alone on the streets for months before she was brought into animal control, she was very close to euthanasia but luckily ma paws and me stepped up for her. She had to go to the vet before she could make her journey to Wisconsin as her spine was completely snapped in half so it needed to be stabilized with pins. She has been with me (her foster) for about 2 months as of February and has been nothing but an amazing joy! She will never walk again but she doesn't care at all, she is only about 8 to 10 months old so this is what she has known most of her life and she has adapted amazingly! She is very easy to get in and out of her chair as she only weighs about 25 pounds and is full grown. Because she is fully paralyzed in her hind extremities she does need help going potty and wears snazzy dippers in the house. expressing her is very simple and only takes a few minutes to do, you can look it up on youtube if you are interested in getting an idea of what it consists of. She sleeps next to a blind 5-pound bunny's pen and lives happily with another dog and 2 cats. she loves going to pet stores and getting lots of attention from people! a few of the people who have cared for her along her journey along with myself believe she may be a good candidate for therapy work if her forever family would like to try that. I know it will take a very special person to adopt this girl but she is so worth it!

Interested in meeting Hope? 

All Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue dogs are in homes with foster families; we do not have a shelter where dogs are available for daily viewing.

Our process is as follows:
1.  Review our policies and adoption radius  on our website: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/
2.  Submit an application for review and approval;
3.  MPM Rescue reviews application and checks vet records and references;
4.  MPM foster contacts approved applicant(s) to arrange a home check and meeting with available dog(s);
5.   If there is a good fit, adoption is completed with a contract and fees (payable via check or cash).

The adoption fee is listed here: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/

Dogs from Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
- Spay/Neuter surgery
- Age appropriate vaccinations
- Heartworm test (for dogs over 6mo) and treatment if positive
- Microchip
- Deworming
- Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
- Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

*Please note that the identified breed(s) are best guesses. We very rarely have information on our dogs' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays.*

animal.description:
Kash and his ears...they take on a life of their own!  He’s an 8 month old Weimaraner/pit mix about 50 lbs, crate trained and learning how to live in a home.  In his former life, he was left tethered outside 24/7.  He was bitten by a snake at one point.  Thank goodness we were able to take him in before he died out there.  He’s a typical energetic puppy, learning to walk on a lead, learning so many new things living inside at the cafe ...but he’s ready for a home of his own.  He will be neutered this week, is heartworm negative and up to date.  This sweetheart is ready for a forever home with a patient and loving family!

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for puppies covers initial deworming,  puppy vaccinations, microchip, and spay/neuter at the rescue's approved vet at 6 months of age. Please see our website for more information.

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
Scarlett is a beautiful, gentle, mellow, and friendly husky girl looking for a new home.

Scarlett is 99% housetrained. She knows that she has to go to the bathroom when out on a walk, and is almost there, but she has had a couple of accidents in the house. She is highly food and treat motivated, and we know this will help her to understand how it all works. She'll get there!

Scarlett isn't a massive fan of her crate yet, this is all quite new to her. She will have a little whine initially, but not for too long. Training, structure and patience (and she said 'also some treats to say thank you!') will really help her learn to relax and not worry so much.

Out and about on walks, she seems uninterested in other dogs in general, but definitely isn't a big fan of cats. She walks nicely on the leash, but you do have to keep alert for seeing cats or squirrels before she does!

Scarlett has a fair amount of energy, and loves a good walk and having some playtime with her people. She really just loves to be around everybody and being part of the conversation, but she's not pushy for affection. If you catch her eye she will roll over and see if you'll give her a belly rub....belly rubs are her favorite thing, right up there with treats!

Scarlett is 4 years old, 50 lbs, and ready for her forever home! Please visit www.liveloveanimalrescue.org to fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
Handsome Malinois Arlo is looking for his forever home, and he comes armed with all manner of good skills.

This guy is not just a pretty face. He is perfectly house trained, he walks beautifully on the leash, and enjoys accompanying you on a car journey. Out and about he is friendly to all new people he meets - and he also doesn't seem to be too bothered by cats, which is always a bonus! He comes when he is called, he loves to be around people, and he's a very gentle, and mellow dog. He will sit calmly next to you and very politely ask for affection. Then if you stop...you will get the little hand nudge to please continue!

Arlo is playful, goody and fun loving, and really enjoys a game of fetch with his people. He is also a big snuggler, and very affectionate and loving.

He absolutely loves to go on a big walks and hikes, and once you get home will pretty much crash out on his bed and chill. He loves his bones, and it's the cutest thing to watch him take his bone back to his bed and then chew away, sometimes upside down with his legs in the air.

Arlo is still a young dog, so has a few minor little issues that may require further training. He is fine to go in his crate, but initially he will complain and have a few grumbles for a few minutes. We think with ongoing structure and being reminded that the crate isn't a bad place to be, he will snap out of that habit.

He also can be a little possessive of his toys...again, he is young and he just needs to learn what is and what isn't acceptable behavior. He is highly treat motivated and he's a smart boy, so we know he can make these changes with patience and training.

All in all, a bright, fun loving, happy go lucky boy with bags of potential, we think Arlo will make somebody a wonderful companion!

Arlo is 1 year old, 81 lbs, and ready for his forever home! Please visit www.liveloveanimalrescue.org to fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
Welcome Brittany!

She is part of our "Chipmunk" Trio!

She is a little over seven weeks old and is doing great. She and her sisters were being given away and we were able to save them thanks to a great supporter who contacted us. Their mom is for sure Husky, but dad we are still contemplating.

These girls are super sweet. They love to play, are very cuddly, love to lay on the couch and in their dog bed, and even have started howling as Husky’s do. They are great with kids, other dogs, and have been socialized very well.

Brittany is the calmer of the bunch. She loves to cuddle and go up the doggie stairs to sleep on the couch. She doesn't look husky, as her spots and face shape show otherwise. Her paws are also somewhat smaller. 

If you are interested in Brittany or her sister Eleanor, fill out an application at our website at www.danteshope.com or message their foster mom Allison at 225-938-6714

animal.description:
Willie's mom (Willa) came to our shelter VERY pregnant and delivered six puppies just days after arriving to her foster home.  The babies struggled a lot in their first three months of life- horrible coccidia, major worm infestations, and a case of parvo that nearly took their lives.  Thanks to an amazing team of volunteers who worked around the clock (and a team of veterinary professionals too), all six puppies (and mom) survived. 

Willie is a handsome boy looking for a forever family. He is 15 weeks old and weighs 18+ pounds.  He is expected to be about 60-70 lbs at adult weight.  His mom is a Rottie/Hound Mix (see photo- Willa) and we don't know a thing about dad.  Based on his size and shape of his head, we're guessing dad was a Mastiff or Great Dane mix.

Willie is neutered; vaccinated for rabies, distemper, and bordetella; and microchipped with a lifetime registration. He is current on flea/tick and prevention too.

Interested in meeting Willie? Please visit our website www.HalfwayHomeRescue.org and complete an adoption application. Adoption donation $550.

We anticipate a LOT of applications for these puppies.  At this time, we are ONLY accepting applications from CT residents.  Applicants must own their homes and be able to provide proof of ownership.  Applications that do not meet the criteria, will not be considered.

animal.description:
***All applications will be considered before inquiries as we do not currently have the staff to respond to every inquiry submitted. 

Please meet Sangria’s babies!  They are typical puppies!  Playful, bouncy, energetic, curious, always starving, and quite simply adorable. They love attention, playing with toys, and love meeting new people. They are working on crate training and on housebreaking. They understand the concept and if consistent, they will head out the door. If they get busy in the toy basket, it might be too late!  They are young and will need supervision and lots of patience. They try so hard and they love treats!  They are learning how to walk on a leash, but with all puppies, will need continued training, consistency and lots and lots of love.  They play well with other dogs, but they have not been formally cat tested. They are a bit excitable about the kitties, so we have just been able to do fence greetings at this time.  

If these pups spark your interest, Then jump in line and apply!  Our app is on the home page, These puppies are gonna fly!

OUR APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PIC OF THE DOG. 

ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:   Tito
Breed:  Collie/Lab mix
Gender:  Male
Age:  3 months
Weight: 15 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current
Heartworm:  Too Young
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with other dogs of various sizes, genders and breeds
Cats:   Yes. They have met cats, but needs a slow meet and greet since they are puppy excitable. Recommend proper intro. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, they have met middle age children and have done well. They have not been tested with infants or toddlers. They are excitable and bouncy at times, and could potentially knock a little one down or get under their feet. 


ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers that work full-time jobs, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description:
Tucker is a gorgeous, sweet, and delightful 2 year old male Cattledog, who is looking for a family to call his own. Tucker came into the shelter as a stray and can be scared of new people but he loves being around other dogs.   We are looking for an active family that has experience with rescues and working dogs.  Tucker will need his family to be patient with him and give him lots of love to overcome his fear and anxiety.  With lots of TLC, he has already bonded really well with his foster mom and loves to play and snuggle with her.  He is slowly getting to know the rest of his foster family.  

Tucker loves being around other dogs. He enjoys long daily walks and playing with his squeaky toys.  He is very receptive to training and is already learning his basic commands. He is on his way to becoming house trained and sleeps through the night in his crate.  The ideal environment for Tucker would be a home with a family that can give him the daily exercise he needs to burn off his energy, and preferably another dog that he can play with and to help him with trusting people more.    

Please fill out an application  at www.carepets.org if you are interested in adopting Tucker. His adoption fee is $700. Please contact the foster home (Sheilly) at sheilly.nayyar@gmail.com,  if you need any additional information about Tucker.

animal.description:
Belle
Female 
Terrier/Jack Russell mix
13 1/2 years
12.8 lbs

My name is Belle.  My owner died and her family could not keep me. I’m so grateful New Hope took me in because a shelter is no place for a golden girl like me. 

My love exploring yards, walks, sleeping at your feet while you work and am very food motivated.  The longer I’m in foster care, the more affectionate I am becoming wanting to be close to my foster an offering her little kisses.  I like to sleep in bed and on a human pillow if you let me. 

I’m fostered with other dogs and cats, and don’t seem super interested in them and co-exist peacefully. 

My mom’s family described me as a little sassy, wanting to do things in my own time and on my own terms.  Foster mom hasn’t really seen that side of me yet.  I do have an adventurous streak so you must keep an eye on me in the yard.   

If I’m taken out for regular potty breaks, I do well.  If you see me sniffing around or acting restless, you know it’s time to take me out. 

I’m not super vocal, but a few times I let foster mom know I didn’t appreciate being confined to a bedroom because I like to be in the middle of the action.  Sometimes I will go off and sleep somewhere. Your clean or dirty laundry pile just might be my favorite spot!

Frannie is a 2 year old sweet, active staffy/pibble girl that loves EVERYONE! 
She loves to play, get attention, and win hearts all around. She is just a classic Good Dog. 

Fit & lean, Frannie loves to zoom around the yard and play nonstop until she collapses, and then she wants snuggles. She thrives off of praise and positive interaction, and will make any lucky family a wonderful companion. She also has the CUTEST little bottom teeth accentuated by a slight underbite, which just makes her even more loveable. If her adopters have children, they will need to be 10+ - Frannie's energy and strength make her better suited for sturdier humans. She is 2 years old but still very young at heart. 

When adopted, Frannie will be spayed, microchipped, UTD on rabies, distemper/parvo, and bordatella vaccines. She is heartworm negative and up to date on flea/tick/heartworm prevention.

Duncan is a beautiful lab/retriever mix. He is 7 months old and ready to start his life with a loving family.

He was kept outside on a chain and it appears that he may have been harassed by other dogs. He needs a proper introduction to other dogs. We would actually suggest that he be the only dog. 

He seems to want to play with some of the larger dogs but then other larger dogs - not so much. The same goes with little dogs. Otherwise he's your typical loving happy puppy. He is up to date on all of his vaccinations and will be neutered before placed in a new home.

Duncan is in South Carolina with our partner rescue. We can arrange a video chat for qualified adopters to observe his behavior and reactivity to other dogs.

If interested in adopting Duncan we can arrange transport with our experienced dog rescue partner Transport person who will negotiate transport fee at a separate charge.

Please submit our adopt application for Duncan - COPY & PASTE the LINK into your browser - we will respond immediately:

animal.description: Shep is a ~10-month old German Shepherd mix who is a very good boy and looking for his new best friend and companion in life. Once Shep bonds with you, he will follow you everywhere and do anything you say. He learns new commands very quickly and just wants to please you. He is extremely high energy, so a yard and active lifestyle are musts. He needs a large amount of exercise and mental stimulation, at least 2 hours of running or playdates every day, but more would be better! He’d be a great running and hiking buddy—he does great off-leash already. He would especially thrive if he could go to work with you and help you throughout your day. He would also love to be trained to perform a more advanced job. For example, I think he’d be a great search and rescue dog. Shep was picked up as a stray by animal control in Clovis, NM and saved by FFTF the day before he was scheduled to be euthanized. As such, he’s dog friendly, but still learning manners around other dogs and hasn’t learned yet when enough is enough. He would love a doggie sibling, but they must be able to keep up with his non-stop energy. He would also do great as an only dog, as his favorite thing will be you! He is house trained, so long as you don’t make him wait too long. He is also crate trained and sleeps very soundly all night in his crate. I think he could be trained to do ok with cats, but he currently has a chase drive with them. He should be fine with older kids. He’s a little mouthy and jumpy right now, but he’s learning quickly to curb those behaviors. He’s around 55 lbs right now and my guess is he will continue growing to be at least 70 lbs. He really can’t wait to meet his forever family and enjoy everything that life in Colorado has to offer!  Apply at fromforgottentoforever.com/adoptionapplication/.
